@NODE "Introduction."

 @{b}1. Introduction.
 ----------------@{ub}

 Ha! Hi there once more. This time I decided polish up all the old
 Amiga-Guide icons still sitting there on my hard drive. I repainted them
 all to fit the new design that was released in "Roman's @{"Magic WB" LINK "What is MagicWB 2.0?"} Icons 8"
 package (get it, it's real artwork! It's somewhere on the aminet named
 `RomIcons8.lha'.)
 Now what do you get:

            * @{b}66 (sixty-six!) Amiga-Guide icons@{ub} according
              to the design mentioned above. (Isn't that just great?
              All your Guide icons, at least most of them, will
              now be in the cool `Roman'-design);
            * @{b}IconUpdate@{ub}, a proggie to easily install these icons
              without losing your tooltypes and preseving the
              position of the icons.

 Well, "this is just some cut, copy and paste work" you say. Indeed it is
 but if nobody does it, then the icons won't start making themselves now,
 will they 8). So, I just took the initiative and here is the result after
 a few days of work.
 Mind you though, I did create some of these Guide icons myself.

 If you don't have @{"MagicWB 2.0" LINK "What is MagicWB 2.0?"} package, then get it now. If you want to
 see the icons in their full glory anyway, just  click the `ClickForColors'
 icon in the `Extras' drawer of this package. If you like the palette and
 want to keep it, you can find the presets in the `Prefs/Env-Archive/sys'
 drawer.

 Well then, enough crap 'n' bollocks, get to work and install these
 babies 8).

 Be see'n ya!

@ENDNODE



@NODE "How to install the icons?"

 @{b}2. How to install the icons?
 ----------------------------@{ub}

 That isn't hard. Just startup the program `IconUpdate' found in the
 `Extras' drawer. Now drop the icon you want on the window and you will
 see the icon image resting there. This is the SOURCE icon.
 The following you should do is drop the DESTINATION icon on the window.
 This is the icon which will be transformed to the new Guide icon.
 After you do this, the window will be cleared and you will see that the
 old icon is magically transformed into the new Guide icon. ALL the tooltypes
 and the position of your icon will NOT be changed! ONLY the image of the
 icon will be replaced.
 Well you have an empty `IconUpdate' window now, so, if you wish, you
 could start all over again with another icon. Have fun!

@ENDNODE



