@NODE "CacheFont"

 @{b}3.5. The "CacheFont" icon.
 --------------------------@{ub}

 This is just a quick one I did. "CacheFont" scans you font directory and
 puts the contents in a file. A patch makes sure the file is read when a
 font requester of somekind pops up and promts for a font. Reading from
 one small file is much faster then from one big directory -- but you
 allready knew that, I guess.

@ENDNODE



